where \$k_{si}, H_{fin}\$, and \$\eta\$ are the thermal conductivity of silicon, fin height and fin efficiency, respectively. \$A_{b}\$ is the base area exposed to fluid, and \$A_{fin}\$ is the total surface area of the pin-fins.
where \$W, L\$ are the width and length of the entire chip; \$W_{s}, L_{s}, P_{w}, P_{l}\$ are the horizontal and vertical spacing and the pitch between pins. \$n\$ is the total number of pins.
